Lime Recruitment is currently working with a Queensland government department
to recruit a Senior Business Analyst contract to 30/06/2024 with possible
extension based in the Brisbane CBD and working from home.

The Senior Business Analyst will report to Project Manager in relation to
project risks, significant development issues and progress against the project
schedule and will be supported by a Principal Project Officer and Change
Manager.

** In this role you will: **

  * Responsible for working with internal customers to help analyse and plan the improvement of processes and data insights, while understanding the opportunities and complexities of the existing workflow platforms and tools. 
  * Lead business stakeholders from across the department for the purposes of engagement, and in conjunction with other Business SMEs and Business Analysts, progress the elicitation of requirements and further definition and refinement of business requirements, confirming proposed designs, and conducting demonstration/review sessions of the working software developed as a result of the design. 
  * Enabling digital product and service delivery capabilities that meet user expectations, building upon investments to date and incorporating contemporary tools and technologies 
  * Explore digital solutions that other land management agencies utilise to understand their potential suitability for the information management and intelligence integration requirements of the client 
  * Ensuring legislative obligations can be further met using an enterprise digital platform which will provide greater insights, ability for re-use, and connected digital assets 

** You will have: **

  * Experience working with government organisations (preferable but not mandatory). 
  * Experience in aspects of systems integration, application ‘look and feel’, development, deployment, and maintenance of applications. 
  * Proficient in applying and adhering to Open Geospatial Consortium (OGC) spatial standards to ensure interoperability and consistency in spatial data handling and analysis. 
  * Experience implementing and optimising solutions for remote work scenarios, ensuring seamless collaboration and data accessibility for distributed teams. 
  * Familiarity with technologies and strategies for overcoming connectivity barriers, such as offline data synchronisation, cloud-based solutions, and efficient use of local resources. 
  * Ability to assess and recommend tools that enhance productivity in remote settings, considering factors such as bandwidth constraints and data security. 

** Queensland based candidates only. **

